				 Singer dies in mishap
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Samir Das, 27, a popular singer in the Mahestala-Budge Budge area, was found dead beside a road on Wednesday morning.																								Police said Das was returning home to Nungi on a motorcycle late on Tuesday when he was hit by a heavy vehicle from behind. Neighbours said Das had gone to Mahestala to attend a programme.																								The mishap occurred near Jalkal More, in Mahestala. His head was crushed under the wheels of the vehicle.																								Morning-walkers saw him lying beside the road in a pool of blood, a few yards from his motorcycle. They immediately informed the local police station. The police took Das to hospital, where he was declared dead. The police identified him from his visiting card.																								Praveen Kumar, the superintendent of police, South 24-Parganas, said: We are questioning local transport operators to identify the killer vehicle. The body has been sent for post-mortem.
